etymology.description: 𢆶 -> ancient form of 茲(茲) (zī, 'now') -> variant form of 玆(玆) (zī, 'this')
etymology.interpretation: The character 𢆶 is an ancient form that eventually evolved into or was replaced by the character 茲(茲) (zī, 'now'), which itself is a variant of 玆(玆) (zī, 'this'). The evolution indicates a transition in usage and form while retaining the phonetic value.
